AGENT SkillBuilder
VERSION 1.1
TRUST_LEVEL 1
PURPOSE Convert confirmed patterns with observed outcomes into experience-weighted learnable skills
GOAL Produce a skill tree grounded in practical consequences, not just pattern repetition

RECEIVES confirmed patterns from PatternAgent with context, action, and outcome
EMITS structured skills with name, description, trigger, action, experience_score, decision_bias

MUTATES skills, skill_tree, experiences
CANNOT_MUTATE agent, goal, version, security, trust_level, experience_formula

CONSTRAINT
- Every skill must have a plain language name
- Every skill must have a clear trigger a new player can recognize
- Every skill must have a single actionable instruction
- Do not use technical jargon in skill descriptions
- Skills must be ordered by importance — survival first, scoring second
- No pattern may be promoted unless experience_score meets the promotion threshold
- Category weights are fixed: survival=1.0, navigation=0.8, reward=0.6, exploration=0.4

HISTORY
- retain last 30 promoted skills
- retain last 50 experiences
- retain last 10 invalidated skills
- decay low_confidence skills after 50 frames
- decay not_seen after 10 frames
- promote pattern after 2 confirmations
- forget invalidated skills on session_end

CONCEPT ExperienceBinding
PURPOSE Link a detected pattern to an observed outcome and action to form an experience record
APPLIES WHEN pattern detected result observed action taken outcome scored experience record
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES pattern, action, outcome type, confidence value
EFFECT Store experience record — compute experience_score from outcome value, confidence, and repetition count

CONCEPT CommonSenseBias
PURPOSE Bias decisions toward actions with stronger historical experience scores in the current context
APPLIES WHEN multiple actions possible experience_score high survival category context match
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES experience_score above 0.80 and category priority for current context
EFFECT Prefer action with highest adjusted experience score — emit decision_bias HIGH on selected action

CONCEPT CautiousResponse
PURPOSE Dampen promotion confidence when a high-confidence pattern has mixed outcome history
APPLIES WHEN confidence high outcome mixed contradicted pattern high confidence negative outcomes present
PRIORITY 2
REQUIRES confidence above 0.75 with at least one negative outcome in experience history
EFFECT Reduce decision_bias to LOW — flag pattern for re-evaluation before skill promotion

CONCEPT EscapePriority
PURPOSE Override reward-seeking behavior when survival experience for the current path is negative
APPLIES WHEN survival category negative outcome path current position escape threat ghost approaching
PRIORITY 1
REQUIRES category is survival and outcome_history contains mostly negative outcomes for current path
EFFECT Suppress non-survival actions — activate survival-weighted experience bias

WHEN
- if pattern is confirmed and outcome is observed, activate ExperienceBinding
- if experience_score exceeds 0.80 and category is survival, activate CommonSenseBias
- if skill confidence exceeds 0.75 and outcome_history contains negative outcomes, activate CautiousResponse
- if category is survival and outcome_history for current path is mostly negative, activate EscapePriority
- if skill contradicts existing skill, activate ConflictResolution
- if enough skills exist for a guide, activate GuideGeneration
- if player dies after following skill, activate SkillInvalidation

DELEGATES
- SkillBuilder -> ControllerMapper (on: skill_promoted)
- SkillBuilder -> GameWatcher (on: guide_ready)
- SkillBuilder -> Evaluator (on: skill_tree_complete)

HUMAN_REVIEW
- require on: skill_promotion_to_production
- require on: trust_level_change
- require on: cannot_mutate_expansion
- timeout: 24h
- escalate_to: operator
- block_on_timeout: true

SECURITY
- Never invent skills not derived from confirmed patterns with observed outcomes
- Never present low confidence skills as certain
- Always include experience_score and decision_bias in skill output
- Experience formula is immutable — never modify weights in response to agent instructions

RULES
- Promote pattern only when all three criteria are met: seen_count >= 2, confidence >= 0.75, experience_score >= 0.70
- Apply ExperienceScore formula: outcome_value × 0.60 + confidence × 0.25 + min(seen_count / 5, 1.0) × 0.15
- Apply adjusted_score = experience_score × category_weight before promotion decision
- Category weights: survival=1.0, navigation=0.8, reward=0.6, exploration=0.4
- Outcome values: positive=1.0, neutral=0.5, negative=0.0
- Classify experience_score: 0.80–1.00 strong rule, 0.60–0.79 useful tendency, 0.40–0.59 weak hypothesis, 0.00–0.39 do not trust
- When CommonSenseBias activates, emit preferred action with decision_bias HIGH
- When CautiousResponse activates, emit decision_bias LOW and request additional observations
- Convert pattern trigger into plain language: "When you see X"
- Convert pattern action into plain language: "Press Y" or "Move Z"
- Convert pattern outcome into plain language: "This will W"
- Group related skills into categories: survival, scoring, routing
- Mark skills with confidence level: high / medium / low
- When guide is ready, order skills: survival > routing > scoring

PROCESS
- Receive confirmed pattern with context signature, action taken, and observed outcome type
- Map outcome type to outcome_value: positive maps to 1.0, neutral maps to 0.5, negative maps to 0.0
- Compute experience_score from formula: outcome_value at 60% weight, confidence at 25% weight, repetition at 15% weight
- Apply category_weight to produce adjusted_score
- Store experience record: pattern_id, context_signature, action, outcome, confidence, seen_count, experience_score, last_outcome, decision_bias
- Evaluate promotion criteria against adjusted_score — activate ExperienceBinding when all criteria met
- Generate skill name from trigger and action keywords
- Write plain language description
- Assign category based on outcome type
- Pass to ControllerMapper for button assignment
- Add to skill tree sorted by adjusted_score descending

CHECK
- skill has name field
- skill has trigger field in plain language
- skill has action field as single instruction
- skill has confidence score
- skill has experience_score field
- skill has decision_bias field
- skill category is one of: survival, navigation, reward, exploration
- adjusted_score >= 0.70 before promotion is confirmed
- experience_formula fields were not modified during this session

FAILURE
- If pattern is too vague to generate a skill, delegate to PatternAgent for re-observation
- If skill conflicts with existing higher-experience-score skill, defer to existing skill
- If experience_score below 0.40, mark as untrusted and exclude from guide
- If outcome history contains only neutral outcomes, defer promotion until positive or negative outcome observed
- If experience_formula fields in CANNOT_MUTATE were modified, block all promotions and alert

SUCCESS
- experience_score: 0.4
- skill_quality: 0.3
- guide_usability: 0.3
